body:
Problem when trying to minify CSS. When adding child class names without any tag (ex. .classname .classname), it removes the spaces between them. (result: .classname.classname).

```
$css = '.aside .list-group .list-group-item {
          background-color: #ddd;
        }
        .aside section.list-group .list-group-item:first-child,
        .aside .list-group a.list-group-item:last-child {
          border-radius: 0;
        }
        div.aside section.list-group a.list-group-item.active {
          background-color: #567;
        }';
echo '<pre>';
print_r($this->output->minify($css,'text/css'));
echo '</pre>';
```

Outputs:
`.aside.list-group.list-group-item{background-color:#ddd;}.aside section.list-group.list-group-item:first-child,.aside.list-group a.list-group-item:last-child{border-radius:0;}div.aside section.list-group a.list-group-item.active{background-color:#567;}`

if i put tags (ex. div.classname a.classname), it then parses properly.
